{"key":"post-15792470","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>15792470</id>\n<content>I had hoped it wouldn't be put to bed, because this bad info comes up way too often.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Bleach is an excellent sanitizer for our clean rooms.&amp;nbsp; Remember, we don't dump our spawn out on the table, so we're not using bleach to 'sterilize'.&amp;nbsp; We clean the table and other surfaces with bleach to knock back 99% or more of the organisms so they don't go airborne during our work and end up in our media.&amp;nbsp; It's about getting rid of the vast majority of contaminants in a work area before starting to up the odds in our favor.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I was able to attain nearly 100% success in a lab with wall to wall carpet and animals in the house, simply by closing the door to the clean room and spraying 10% bleach solution into the air, allowing it to settle to the carpeted floor below, taking contaminants with it prior to work.&amp;nbsp; This 'washed' the air, and the bleach-damp carpet kept them contained while I work.&amp;nbsp; I always do this as a pre-wash before using the flow hood or glovebox.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>15792526</next>\n<prev>15784507</prev>\n<first>15782508</first>\n<last>17157452</last>\n<when>1328988582</when>\n<utime>02/11/12 09:29 PM</utime>\n</post>"}